<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Interreg</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p>&nbsp;<img alt="Kart over norsk deltagelse i EUs grenseregionale og transnasjonale programmer 2007-2013" src="/upload/KRD/Temabilder/REGA/Kart_537x375.gif" /></p>
<p><strong>Interreg is the EU programme for promoting social and economic cross-border integration via regional cooperation.</strong> </p>
<p>The programme was established in 1991 to strengthen cooperation between neighbouring regions divided by national borders, within and bordering the EU. Norway has participated in the Interreg cooperation since 1996. The present programme period expires in 2013.</p>
<p><strong>Norway is inolved in 11 Interreg programmes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Four boundary regional programmes along the borders with Finland, Sweden and Denmark (North, Bothnia-Atlantica, Sweden-Norway and Øresund-Kattegat-Skagerrak) </li>
<li>Three trans-national programmes (the Baltic Sea, the North Sea and the Northern Periphery) </li>
<li>Four pan-European programmes (ESPON, Interact, Interreg IVC and URBACT II).</li></ul>
<p>Furthermore, Norway participates in a boundary regional cooperation with Russia, under the auspices of the EU’s European Neighbourhood and Partnership Instrument (ENPI). The Norwegian government’s share of the European territorial cooperation for the entire programme period from 2007 to 2013 will amount to around NOK 730 million. </p>
<p>Information on the individual programmes is available at <a href="http://www.interreg.no">www.interreg.no</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
